rows.text:
Kitab al-Jim{{#tag:ref| The name means "Book of the [[Ǧīm|Jim (Letter)]]". |group=n}}
({{lang-ar|كتاب الجيم}})
a.k.a. Kitab al-Lughat or Kitab al-Huruf

Al-Jamhara al-Lugha{{#tag:ref| The name means "Collection of Language". |group=n}}
({{lang-ar|جمهرة اللغة}})
a.k.a. Al-Jamhara fi al-Lugha (The all-embracing in language)

Taj al-Lugha wa Sihah al-Arabiyya{{#tag:ref| The name means "The crown of Language and the authentic of Arabic". |group=n}}
({{lang-ar|تاج اللغة وصحاح العربية}})
shorter title: Taj al-Lugha or al-Sihah

Al-Muhkam wa al-Muhit al-A'zam{{#tag:ref| The name means "The arbitrator and the Great Ocean". |group=n}}
({{lang-ar|المحكم والمحيط الأعظم}})
shorter title: Al-Muhkam

Al-Qamus al-Muhit wa al-Qabus al-Wasit{{#tag:ref| Al-Qamus al-Muhit means "The surrounding Ocean". |group=n}} {{#tag:ref| '''The Qamus''' - which may be derived from [[Greek language|Greek]] ''okeanos'' became, and has remained, the commonest [[Arabic language|Arabic]] word for dictionary. |group=n}}
({{lang-ar|القاموس المحيط، والقابوس الوسيط}})
shorter title: Al-Qamus al-Muhit

Taj al-Arus Min Jawahir al-Qamus{{#tag:ref| The name means "The bride's crown from the pearls of the Qamus (Ocean)". |group=n}}
({{lang-ar|تاج العروس}})
shorter title: Taj al-Arus

Muhit al-Muhit{{#tag:ref| The name means "Circumference of the Ocean". |group=n}}
({{lang-ar|محيط المحيط}})
a.k.a. Qutr al-Muhit (The Diameter of the Ocean)
